        <description>The sequel to &lt;a href="/game/archon-the-light-and-the-dark"&gt;Archon&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;i&gt;Archon II: Adept&lt;/i&gt; features a more complex board and enhanced gameplay.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Each side plays as an Adept - a powerful wizard with the ability to cast spells against other Adepts and his summonings - and must defeat the other side, either Chaos or Order, by attacking him/her with summoned Elementals or Demons. Each side can summon 4 unique elementals at a time or choose from 4 demons, common to both.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Gameplay is similar to the original, reminiscent of a chess-like board game, requiring strategy, but with arcade elements, especially when two adepts confront each other face-to-face. The board also shifts from time to time, making the strategy less predictable.</description>
